latestPosts.caption:
#WMGRealStories: For her Mandap Muhurat, Avani, draped in a red bandhani saree and wearing gold jewellery her mother had once worn as a bride herself, embodied grace, memory, and quiet strength. “Mummy is not here with me today, but I feel her in every part of this moment
—in my heart, in my smile, in the love that surrounds me. I know she’s with me, proud and watching, every step of the way,” she shared.
As she walked down the aisle holding her mother’s photo, flanked by her father and younger brother, it wasn’t just a wedding-it was a moment of remembrance and love.

Shot by @playthenovel
Bride @avani_j
Jewellery @manubhaijewels
